scovered in burgan oilfield.' b'' b'[1938] the first general elections, resulted in the first' b'legislative council.' b'' b'[1942] the first bank in kuwait was opened.' b'' b"[1945] ``kuwait house'' was established in egypt to look after" b'kuwaiti missions and interests.' b'' b'[1946] the first kuwaiti crude oil shipment was exported.' b'' b"[1948] ``kazima magazine'' was issued, the first kuwaiti magazine" b'to be both printed and published in kuwait.' b'' b'[1950] sheikh ahmed al-jaber al-sabah, who had ruled kuwait for' b'thirty years, died.' b'' b'[1951] may kuwait radio went on the air for the first time.' b'' b"[1952] the first ``kuwait masterplan'' was drawn up." b'' b'[1954] khalid al-faraj, the man of letters and poet, died.' b'' b"[1954] december, ``kuwait al-youm'' (official gazette) was" b'issued for the first time.' b'' b'[1955] oil was struck in al-rawdhatain, north of kuwait.' b'' b'[1957] kuwait wall was demolished and removed.' b'' b"[1957] the ``social affairs department'' conducted the first" b'population census.' b'' b"[1958] december the first issue of ``al-arabi'' magazine was" b'published.' b'' b'[1960] the first kuwaiti woman was employed by kuwait oil' b'company.' b'' b'[1961] april the kuwaiti dinar became the official currency' b'in kuwait.' b'' b'[1961] june the agrrement of january concluded' b'between kuwait and great britain, was terminated.' b'' b'[1961] july kuwait became a member of the arab league.' b'' b'[1961] december, kuwait fund for arab economic development' b'was established.' b'' b'[1962] january the elected constituent assembly met to draw' b'up the constitution of kuwait.' b'' b'[1962] an amiri decree was issued providing for the division of' b'the country into three governorates.' b'' b'[1962] november the amir of kuwait, sheikh abdulla al-salem' b'al-sabah ratified the first constitution of kuwait.' b'' b'[1963] january. the first elected national assembly of kuwait' b'convened.' b'' b'[1963] may kuwait became a membe